# ECC-vendored language rules (cpp/ python/ rust/ typescript/) are installer-
# managed: ecc-install / ecc-update re-vendor them from the ECC repo via `cp -R`,
# byte-identical to upstream. They are reproducible and not ours, so they live on
# disk but stay untracked -- the same model already used for ECC skills
# (claude/skills/.gitignore) and ECC commands/agents/hooks. Each carries a
# `paths:` frontmatter, so they load only when files of that language are open.
#
# ECC's common/ and web/ rules are deliberately NOT vendored: they have no
# `paths:` field and would load into every session, and much of that content is
# generic or stale for the current model. Our own always-on guidance lives in
# claude/rules/shared/ instead. See ECC_VENDOR_LANGS in zsh/functions.zsh.
#
# Only our OWN custom rules are version-controlled. Put them under
# claude/rules/shared/ (outside the ECC lang dirs, which ecc-sync-rules wipes
# with `rm -rf` on every sync) and they are tracked by the whitelist below.
/*
!/.gitignore
!/shared/
